I'm enrolling you in charm school.

1168
01:11:29,065 --> 01:11:31,693
I have to say what I think.
I can't work this way.

1169
01:11:31,867 --> 01:11:34,768
You can't work this way?
You've been a songwriter for six days.

1170
01:11:34,937 --> 01:11:36,700
God created the universe in six days.

1171
01:11:36,872 --> 01:11:41,104
And he never had a hit. Okay, he did.
He had "He's Got the Whole World in..."

1172
01:11:41,277 --> 01:11:42,767
I'm going to the party.

1173
01:11:42,945 --> 01:11:46,005
You are not going to the party.
You, young lady, are grounded.

1174
01:11:46,182 --> 01:11:48,412
You're grounded. Come back here.

1175
01:11:48,584 --> 01:11:51,917
- Please. I'm a little bit desperate. Please.
- I'll see you there.

1176
01:11:52,088 --> 01:11:55,956
You won't. You won't because
you're not invited. They won't let you in.

1177
01:12:10,373 --> 01:12:12,534
- Hey, Ray.
- Alex, my man.

1178
01:12:12,708 --> 01:12:14,972
- How are you?
- I'm good, man. How you doing?

1179
01:12:15,144 --> 01:12:16,406
So is Sophie here?

1180
01:12:16,579 --> 01:12:19,173
You know what?
I haven't seen her. Yeah.

1181
01:12:19,348 --> 01:12:20,713
- Chris?
- Who?

1182
01:12:20,883 --> 01:12:23,113
- You know, my manager.
- I'm sorry. Have fun.

1183
01:12:23,285 --> 01:12:26,413
- Yeah.
- Hey, Michelle. Good to see you, babe.

1184
01:12:26,589 --> 01:12:27,578
Hey, how's it going?

1185
01:12:32,528 --> 01:12:34,393
Hey, Ray, what's up, man?

1186
01:12:34,930 --> 01:12:36,557
How's it going?

1187
01:13:02,024 --> 01:13:03,013
Hey.

1188
01:13:03,192 --> 01:13:04,523
- Where's Sophie?
- Hang on.

1189
01:13:05,127 --> 01:13:08,790
Hang on. God, she's here. Please
don't let her through. Don't let her through.

1190
01:13:08,964 --> 01:13:11,728
We cannot let her talk to Cora.
She's gonna ruin everything.

1191
01:13:11,901 --> 01:13:13,630
- Who?
- Sophie. She hates the song.

1192
01:13:13,803 --> 01:13:16,294
- She hates the song you wrote?
- Yes. She hates it.

1193
01:13:16,472 --> 01:13:19,669
But she wrote the song.
Why does she hate it?

1194
01:13:19,842 --> 01:13:22,276
We had a little disagreement.

1195
01:13:22,445 --> 01:13:24,037
Hi there, Soph, how are you?

1196
01:13:24,213 --> 01:13:26,443
- Hey, Sophie.
- Good evening.

1197
01:13:26,615 --> 01:13:29,448
So you brought something,
did you, Sophie?

1198
01:13:29,618 --> 01:13:32,416
Yes. My mother told me,
"Never go to a party empty-handed"...

1199
01:13:32,588 --> 01:13:37,048
...so I went to the Zen Eatery and got
a selection of cookies. No, thank you.

1200
01:13:37,226 --> 01:13:38,887
Nirvana Nougat.

1201
01:13:43,666 --> 01:13:45,827
Hey. It's my favorite writers.

1202
01:13:46,001 --> 01:13:47,332
Hi, C. How are you?

1203
01:13:47,503 --> 01:13:49,494
We brought you some cookies,
from all of us.

1204
01:13:50,072 --> 01:13:52,336
Thank you. Derek.

1205
01:13:52,508 --> 01:13:54,271
Cora, I really wanted to talk to you...

1206
01:13:54,443 --> 01:13:56,911
About the fact that
we're gonna have to leave early...

1207
01:13:57,079 --> 01:13:59,741
...to finish this song
which has become important to us...

1208
01:13:59,915 --> 01:14:01,906
...in both an artistic and spiritual sense.

1209
01:14:02,084 --> 01:14:04,314
You can't leave yet. Come see the house.

1210
01:14:04,487 --> 01:14:07,615
I wanna show you the roof. It's upstairs.

1211
01:14:07,790 --> 01:14:09,985
Do you know...? Well...

1212
01:14:12,728 --> 01:14:17,165
Cora, I definitely see how much
you've thought about the song and...

1213
01:14:17,333 --> 01:14:20,666
Great roof. In a very interesting place
as well, right at the top...

1214
01:14:20,836 --> 01:14:24,294
- Sophie was about to say something.
- Was she? I don't think she was. No.

1215
01:14:24,473 --> 01:14:27,499
She looks like she's about
to say something, then just... clams up.

1216
01:14:27,676 --> 01:14:32,079
What I wanted to say is that I appreciate
that you're bringing thought to the music...

1217
01:14:32,248 --> 01:14:36,082
...but I really and honestly feel
that we're pandering.

1218
01:14:38,454 --> 01:14:42,185
Which means trying to make others like you,
which I think is a really nice thing.

1219
01:14:42,358 --> 01:14:45,054
I do a lot of it.
"Just going out pandering, be back soon."

1220
01:14:45,227 --> 01:14:49,630
The song is about the struggle, you know,
to show your true feelings.

1221
01:14:49,798 --> 01:14:52,733
And your very confident sexual display...

1222
01:14:52,902 --> 01:14:56,895
...is, you know, a total contradiction
of the fear and insecurity.

1223
01:14:57,072 --> 01:15:00,235
No, I don't think so.
And my fans really love it when I dance.

1224
01:15:00,409 --> 01:15:02,707
- You're a wonderful dancer.
- That's a fair point.

1225
01:15:02,878 --> 01:15:06,245
- My last CD only went to number two.
- But in this case, if you trust us...

1226
01:15:06,415 --> 01:15:10,044
And Shakira is breathing down my neck.
So I wanna dance.

1227
01:15:12,087 --> 01:15:14,351
You shall dance.

1228
01:15:14,990 --> 01:15:19,290
But thank you for your honesty, Sophie.
Cherish your passion.

1229
01:15:19,461 --> 01:15:23,329
- Well, thank you.
- Cora, Timberlake's here. Wants to say hi.

1230
01:15:23,599 --> 01:15:25,396
Nice to see you, C. Talk to you later.

1231
01:15:25,568 --> 01:15:27,832
And I'm looking forward
to the new last verse.

1232
01:15:28,003 --> 01:15:29,197
- Cora, wait.
- It's over.

1233
01:15:29,371 --> 01:15:31,965
It was a very nice try,
but you have hit the karmic wall.

1234
01:15:32,141 --> 01:15:36,202
With no help from you.
You just stood there. Talk about pandering.

1235
01:15:36,378 --> 01:15:39,040
I did not pander. I just told her
what she wanted to hear.

1236
01:15:39,215 --> 01:15:41,615
- I'm gonna go tell her the truth.
- You just did.

1237
01:15:41,784 --> 01:15:44,378
Are you gonna use flash cards this time?
You're stubborn.

1238
01:15:44,553 --> 01:15:47,522
And you're not stubborn enough
to stand up for what's good.

1239
01:15:47,690 --> 01:15:50,921
I mean, I just don't wanna see you
do what you did on your solo album.

1240
01:15:51,093 --> 01:15:52,424
Yes, yes, yes.

1241
01:15:53,896 --> 01:15:56,364
I bought it. The last copy.

1242
01:15:57,266 --> 01:15:59,860
All right, well, I insist
on paying you back immediately.

1243
01:16:00,035 --> 01:16:01,468
9.99, right? Do you have a penny?

1244
01:16:01,637 --> 01:16:04,299
You were trying so hard to get a hit
that it wasn't you.

1245
01:16:04,473 --> 01:16:06,566
The songs were soulless.

1246
01:16:06,742 --> 01:16:09,370
I agree. But ours has soul, so...

1247
01:16:09,545 --> 01:16:12,878
But not if we ruin it. And you know that.
Why are you so scared to care?

1248
01:16:13,048 --> 01:16:15,141
Because it won't matter.

1249
01:16:15,317 --> 01:16:19,219
Because behind
all her Buddhism-in-a-thong philosophy...

1250
01:16:19,388 --> 01:16:22,653
...what she cares about
is seats filled and units sold.

1251
01:16:22,825 --> 01:16:24,486
Nothing's gonna make her your pal...

1252
01:16:24,660 --> 01:16:26,958
...any more than years with Colin
made him mine.

1253
01:16:27,129 --> 01:16:29,563
Because in the end, it's all just business.

1254
01:16:29,732 --> 01:16:31,632
- What is?
- All of it. Everything.

1255
01:16:31,800 --> 01:16:33,768
That's why they call it
the music business.

1256
01:16:33,936 --> 01:16:36,700
It's a good thing.
I wish everything in life was that clear.

1257
01:16:36,872 --> 01:16:39,340
I want something from you,
you want something from me.

1258
01:16:39,508 --> 01:16:41,032
No false promises or expectations.

1259
01:16:44,647 --> 01:16:46,114
Well.

1260
01:16:46,282 --> 01:16:48,512
Congratulations on your feel-good song.

1261
01:16:51,353 --> 01:16:52,877
Can I get you a drink?

1262
01:17:20,382 --> 01:17:23,351
There's plenty of time.
We have the night, part of the morning...

1263
01:17:23,519 --> 01:17:25,419
...teeniest little bit of the afternoon.

1264
01:17:54,950 --> 01:17:57,441
I can't read it.
What does that...? What does that say?

1265
01:17:58,187 --> 01:18:00,087
"Sorry, I can't do this."

1266
01:18:05,194 --> 01:18:09,130
<i>Sorry, I can't do this</i>

1267
01:18:10,666 --> 01:18:14,102
Not sure about the scansion.
What...? What, are you leaving?

1268
01:18:14,269 --> 01:18:18,467
Yeah. I'm sorry.
Maybe I'll think of something later.

1269
01:18:18,640 --> 01:18:21,302
There is no later.
She needs the song tomorrow.

1270
01:18:21,477 --> 01:18:24,412
If we don't give it to her,
she's gonna go to someone else.

1271
01:18:24,580 --> 01:18:25,945
I will have lost the job.

1272
01:18:26,115 --> 01:18:28,242
I'm sorry.

1273
01:18:29,051 --> 01:18:31,781
- Okay, look.
- No, I want to help. I do.

1274
01:18:31,954 --> 01:18:34,252
I wanna help you finish, but I can't.

1275
01:18:34,423 --> 01:18:38,723
I can't write when I feel like this.
I'm not inspired.

1276
01:18:38,894 --> 01:18:43,263
I don't care. I don't care if you're inspired.
Inspiration's for amateurs.

1277
01:18:43,432 --> 01:18:46,924
I just want four lines. Please.
I just want four lines.

1278
01:18:47,102 --> 01:18:49,969
- I can't.
- Oh, but you can and you won't.

1279
01:18:50,139 --> 01:18:53,506
- Are you saying I wanted this to happen?
- I'm saying that's what you do.

1280
01:18:53,675 --> 01:18:56,007
You push and push
and move the furniture around...

1281
01:18:56,178 --> 01:18:57,873
...and talk all the time...

1282
01:18:58,046 --> 01:19:00,480
...and screw everything up
just like he said.

1283
01:19:00,949 --> 01:19:03,611
Who's he? What are you talking about?
What are you saying?

1284
01:19:03,786 --> 01:19:06,550
I read the book because I wanted
to come to you and say:

1285
01:19:06,722 --> 01:19:10,453
"You're not at all like Sally Michaels."
But actually, he's got you spot on.

1286
01:19:10,626 --> 01:19:14,187
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying Sloan Cates was right.

1287
01:19:15,264 --> 01:19:19,257
Oh, my God. Please take that back.

1288
01:19:19,435 --> 01:19:22,893
The poor, innocent, helpless
"'I can't write,' she says to herself" girl...

1289
01:19:23,071 --> 01:19:25,096
...has co-authored
three-quarters of a hit...

1290
01:19:25,274 --> 01:19:28,402
...and is holding it ransom
because she can't get what she wants.

1291
01:19:28,577 --> 01:19:32,035
You think life is this fairy tale.

1292
01:19:32,214 --> 01:19:35,843
When it turns out that everything
doesn't end happily, you can't deal with it.

1293
01:19:57,105 --> 01:20:02,407
<i>Mama says I can't, Daddy says I can</i>
<i>Nut now my body just wants to slam</i>

1294
01:20:03,679 --> 01:20:05,203
<i>Slam</i>

1295
01:20:06,181 --> 01:20:09,548
- C, Alex Fletcher is here.
- Hey, Alex.

1296
01:20:10,018 --> 01:20:13,249
C, could l...? Could I have a quick word?
Thanks a lot.

1297
01:20:13,622 --> 01:20:16,022
- Derek, how are you? Good to see you.
- Alex Fletcher.

1298
01:20:19,061 --> 01:20:21,154
Yo, so how's my girl Sophie, man?

1299
01:20:21,330 --> 01:20:23,958
Yeah, no, she's keeping it pretty real.

1300
01:20:24,132 --> 01:20:25,827
Yeah, what a girl.

1301
01:20:26,001 --> 01:20:30,062
C, hi. Listen, it's about
the new last verse.

1302
01:20:30,239 --> 01:20:33,299
It's not completely formed
in the classical sense yet.

1303
01:20:33,475 --> 01:20:36,933
It's more a kind of string of words
that you can connect in almost any way.

1304
01:20:37,112 --> 01:20:39,376
- I think it's quite innovative.
- I got the lyrics.

1305
01:20:39,548 --> 01:20:43,279
Sophie faxed them over this morning.
They are so beautiful.

1306
01:20:43,452 --> 01:20:45,716
It's what I always wanted to say
to my boyfriend.

1307
01:20:45,888 --> 01:20:48,721
It's the perfect end to the song.

1308
01:20:49,091 --> 01:20:53,721
<i>There are moments</i>
<i>When I don't know if it's real</i>

1309
01:20:53,896 --> 01:20:58,731
<i>Or if anybody feels the way I feel</i>

1310
01:20:58,901 --> 01:21:01,961
<i>I need inspiration</i>

1311
01:21:02,738 --> 01:21:08,472
<i>Not just another negotiation</i>

1312
01:21:10,112 --> 01:21:15,448
<i>All I wanna do</i>
<i>Is find a way back into...</i>

1313
01:21:16,618 --> 01:21:19,178
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, yeah. Sorry, sorry.

1314
01:21:19,354 --> 01:21:22,448
I just... I just completely,
I don't know, spaced out.

1315
01:21:22,624 --> 01:21:25,354
That's okay. Let's take it from the top
with the new intro.

1316
01:21:25,527 --> 01:21:27,324
Yep. Great.

1317
01:21:29,231 --> 01:21:33,327
<i>Yeah, Cora Corman and Alex Fletcher</i>

1318
01:21:33,502 --> 01:21:35,493
<i>Way back into love</i>

1319
01:21:41,143 --> 01:21:42,132
Hi.

1320
01:21:42,778 --> 01:21:44,336
Hello.

1321
01:21:45,047 --> 01:21:48,949
I bought these for your children because
one should never show up empty-handed.

1322
01:21:49,518 --> 01:21:53,887
They're aliens.
Clearly, I have no children. Here.

1323
01:21:54,056 --> 01:21:56,854
- Here, let me get that for you.
- Thank you.

1324
01:21:59,995 --> 01:22:03,487
I am gonna go to the office.

1325
01:22:04,099 --> 01:22:06,863
- I am too. Have fun with those.
- Bye.

1326
01:22:13,175 --> 01:22:15,439
Put them there, thanks.

1327
01:22:17,479 --> 01:22:19,208
You coming to the concert tomorrow?

1328
01:22:19,648 --> 01:22:21,707
Can't disappoint Lucy.

1329
01:22:21,883 --> 01:22:24,078
Yes, yes, very important.

1330
01:22:24,987 --> 01:22:29,651
Chris is bringing his daughter as well,
so should be fun.

1331
01:22:29,992 --> 01:22:32,927
I just wanted to say
I thought your last verse was fantastic.

1332
01:22:33,362 --> 01:22:34,351
Thank you, Alex.

1333
01:22:35,330 --> 01:22:37,662
And I'm very sorry about what I said.

1334
01:22:37,833 --> 01:22:41,462
Well, you know, life isn't a fairy tale
and I have to grow up...

1335
01:22:41,637 --> 01:22:43,502
...and I'm gonna do that in Florida.

1336
01:22:44,172 --> 01:22:46,140
Well, that's just ridiculous.

1337
01:22:46,308 --> 01:22:49,573
No one grows up in Florida.
Unless they're an orange.

1338
01:22:49,745 --> 01:22:52,543
Well, I'm managing
the new Weight-Not branch in Boca Raton.

1339
01:22:52,714 --> 01:22:55,376
You should be writing,
not fighting cellulite.

1340
01:22:55,550 --> 01:22:58,110
Well, I can do both.
We need a new marketing campaign.

1341
01:22:58,286 --> 01:23:00,049
Swimsuit season is coming up.

1342
01:23:01,623 --> 01:23:03,215
Thing is...

1343
01:23:04,626 --> 01:23:06,719
...I can't...

1344
01:23:10,298 --> 01:23:12,596
...compose without you.

1345
01:23:12,768 --> 01:23:15,635
Thanks, but I don't think
it's a good idea.

1346
01:23:20,509 --> 01:23:22,374
All right. You're obviously very busy.

1347
01:23:27,816 --> 01:23:29,408
Good luck.

1348
01:23:30,252 --> 01:23:31,549
You too.

1349
01:25:18,827 --> 01:25:20,488
Cora!

1350
01:25:24,966 --> 01:25:27,696
- Gracie, aren't you excited?
- Let's go.

1351
01:25:29,404 --> 01:25:33,397
You know what? You guys, just go.
I think I'm gonna skip it.

1352
01:25:33,575 --> 01:25:36,043
- No, come on. You can't skip it.
- You know what, kids?

1353
01:25:36,211 --> 01:25:38,679
I'm gonna talk to your aunt, okay?
Gary, take them in.

1354
01:25:38,847 --> 01:25:40,872
- Should I meet you...?
- Do it. How hard is it?

1355
01:25:41,049 --> 01:25:42,539
- Go, walk, sit.
- Find your seats.

1356
01:25:42,717 --> 01:25:45,652
Honey, I need a second. Thank you.
Love you. You're a good man.

1357
01:25:45,821 --> 01:25:47,015
Now, listen to me.

1358
01:25:47,189 --> 01:25:51,751
Those kids have told all of their friends
that their aunt wrote Cora's new hit song.

1359
01:25:51,927 --> 01:25:54,521
And they wanna share this with you.
You gotta go in.

1360
01:25:54,696 --> 01:25:57,631
Yeah. No, I know. I know. I just...

1361
01:25:57,799 --> 01:26:01,530
I don't know how I'm gonna go in there
and look at him.

1362
